                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/973</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Peruvian Chargé</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FSMd1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Freyre</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Chargé d’Affaires of Peru presents his compliments to the Honorable the
                    Secretary of State, and acting under instructions from his Government has the
                    honor to inform him that the Governments of Bolivia, Brazil, Ecuador, and
                    Uruguay have advised the Government of Peru they accept the Peruvian plan to
                    attend the congress of Buenos Aires, as outlined in the Legation’s memorandum of
                    the 14th instant.</p>
                <p>The Government of Argentina, however, has hitherto refrained from replying to the
                    Peruvian propositions submitted by the Minister of Peru at Buenos Aires.</p>
            </div>
